    "image_with_text_t6KzFw": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_CcwiLn": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Content creator Ryan Lopes <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/rylopes/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://www.instagram.com/rylopes/\">(@rylopes)</a> has been shaping his creative world for over a decade; blending lifestyle, beauty, fashion, and still life photography into a voice that’s distinctly his own. His work moves <a href=\"https://open.spotify.com/user/1278484302\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://open.spotify.com/user/1278484302\">across mediums</a>, guided by curiosity. Timeless, fluid, and effortlessly thoughtful,  he creates a space that explores the intersections of taste, truth, and self-expression. We caught up with Ryan to explore what fuels his creative practice. </p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "text_CcwiLn"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "image": "shopify://shop_images/IMG_7650_2.jpg",
        "height": "adapt",
        "desktop_image_width": "medium",
        "layout": "image_first",
        "desktop_content_position": "middle",
        "desktop_content_alignment": "left",
        "content_layout": "no-overlap",
        "color_scheme": "scheme-1",
        "mobile_content_alignment": "left",
        "padding_top": 36,
        "padding_bottom": 36
      }
    },
    "image_with_text_wKVLmh": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_CLbqn8": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Q: </strong>Tell us the story behind @rylopes.</p><p><strong>A: </strong>I started sharing content through Instagram about ten years ago, and really began to grow a voice and audience during the summer of 2018. Fast forward to 2020 and the influence of the pandemic, I grew more within my craft, expanding and exploring my medium of photography, styling, overall strutting this lifestyle of my own that is driven by art, design, rituals and expression(s).</p><p><strong>Q: </strong>How would you describe your style?</p><p><strong>A: </strong>Tailored, timeless, fluid, yet modest.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "text_CLbqn8"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "image": "shopify://shop_images/Screenshot_2025-10-01_at_2.15.43_PM.png",
        "height": "adapt",
        "desktop_image_width": "medium",
        "layout": "text_first",
        "desktop_content_position": "middle",
        "desktop_content_alignment": "left",
        "content_layout": "no-overlap",
        "color_scheme": "scheme-1",
        "mobile_content_alignment": "left",
        "padding_top": 0,
        "padding_bottom": 36
      }
    },
    "image_with_text_NjQ3EM": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_ENV8fL": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Q:</strong> Where do you go when you are looking for inspiration?</p><p><strong>A:</strong> I go to music. I revise my old work and think of how I felt then. I have conversations. I look to print for previous eras of art and creativity. I love to challenge myself in observing things that already were.</p><p></p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "text_ENV8fL"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "image": "shopify://shop_images/IMG_7651.jpg",
        "height": "adapt",
        "desktop_image_width": "medium",
        "layout": "image_first",
